<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
<div class="how-it-works" id="how">
  <div class="section-header" style="text-align:center;">
    <div class="eyebrow">Methodology</div>
    <h2>From raw transactions<br>to <em>pricing decisions</em></h2>
    <p class="section-desc">PriceIQ follows a rigorous 4-step pipeline derived directly from your customer shopping data — cleaning, engineering, modelling, and recommending.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="steps-grid">
    <div class="step reveal">
      <div class="step-num">01</div>
      <span class="step-icon">🧹</span>
      <h3>Data Cleaning & Prep</h3>
      <p>Parse invoice dates, deduplicate records, and drop identifier columns like <code style="font-family:DM Mono,monospace;font-size:11px;color:#f0d9a8">invoice_no</code> and <code style="font-family:DM Mono,monospace;font-size:11px;color:#f0d9a8">customer_id</code> that add noise without signal.</p>
      <span class="step-tag">df.drop_duplicates()</span>
    </div>
    <div class="step reveal">
      <div class="step-num">02</div>
      <span class="step-icon">⚙️</span>
      <h3>Feature Engineering</h3>
      <p>Compute unit prices, categorise average transaction values as High/Low, classify mall traffic as High / Moderate / Low, and encode payment methods numerically.</p>
      <span class="step-tag">pd.factorize() · pd.merge()</span>
    </div>
    <div class="step reveal">
      <div class="step-num">03</div>
      <span class="step-icon">🌲</span>
      <h3>Random Forest Modelling</h3>
      <p>Two models: a <strong>Regressor</strong> to predict price, and a <strong>Classifier</strong> to assign price categories (Low / Medium / High) using sklearn Pipelines with standard scaling and one-hot encoding.</p>
      <span class="step-tag">RandomForestClassifier · Pipeline</span>
    </div>
    <div class="step reveal">
      <div class="step-num">04</div>
      <span class="step-icon">💰</span>
      <h3>Heuristic Price Optimisation</h3>
      <p>Infer price sensitivity per category. Apply ±5% directional adjustments and project hypothetical revenue — giving a clear, actionable recommendation for each category.</p>
      <span class="step-tag">infer_sensitivity() · suggest_optimal_price()</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

